I will try and keep it brief.<br />
Last year (august) I bought a beautiful Focus Izalco Max from a well-known bike shop (shopP) 100 miles from where I live.<br />
Beautiful ride, but it soon developed creaks. I eliminated these by greasing the headset and bb assembly  - it has one one these one-piece bb axles and spider - two dead easy jobs. But I also had a great deal of trouble getting the rear <a href="http://road.cc/content/news/128748-video-hands-new-focus-rat-rapid-axle-technology-thru-axle" target="_blank" class="externalLink" rel="nofollow">RAT...</a><br />
